#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:4
msgid "Using profiles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:6
msgid ""
"So far we have used the default settings stored in ``~/.conan/profiles/"
"default`` and defined as command line arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:8
msgid ""
"However, configurations can be large, settings can be very different, and we "
"might want to switch easily between different configurations with different "
"settings, options, etc. The best way to do it is using profiles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:11
msgid ""
"A profile file contains a predefined set of ``settings``, ``options``, "
"``environment variables``, and ``build_requires`` and has this structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:14
msgid ""
"[settings]\n"
"setting=value\n"
"\n"
"[options]\n"
"MyLib:shared=True\n"
"\n"
"[env]\n"
"env_var=value\n"
"\n"
"[build_requires]\n"
"Tool1/0.1@user/channel\n"
"Tool2/0.1@user/channel, Tool3/0.1@user/channel\n"
"*: Tool4/0.1@user/channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:30
msgid ""
"Options allow definition with wildcards, to apply same option value to many "
"packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:32
msgid ""
"[options]\n"
"*:shared=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:37
msgid "They would contain the desired configuration, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:39
msgid "*clang_3.5*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:39
msgid ""
" [settings]\n"
" os=Macos\n"
" arch=x86_64\n"
" compiler=clang\n"
" compiler.version=3.5\n"
" compiler.libcxx=libstdc++11\n"
" build_type=Release\n"
"\n"
" [env]\n"
" CC=/usr/bin/clang\n"
" CXX=/usr/bin/clang++"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:54
msgid ""
"You can store them in the default profile folder or anywhere in you project "
"and you can use it instead of command line arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:56
msgid "$ conan create demo/testing -pr=clang_3.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:60
msgid ""
"If we continue with the example of Poco, we could have a handy profile to "
"help us build our project with the desired configuration and avoid the usage "
"of all the command line arguments when installing the dependency packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:63
msgid ""
"A profile to install dependencies as **shared** and in **debug** mode will "
"look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:65
msgid "*debug_shared*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:65
msgid ""
" include(default)\n"
"\n"
" [settings]\n"
" build_type=Debug\n"
"\n"
" [options]\n"
" Poco:shared=True\n"
" Poco:enable_apacheconnector=False\n"
" OpenSSL:shared=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:78
msgid "With this we could just install using the profile:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:80
msgid "$ conan install . -pr=debug_shared"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:84
msgid ""
"We could also create a new profile to use a different compiler version and "
"store it in our project directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:86
msgid "*poco_clang_3.5*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:86
msgid ""
" include(clang_3.5)\n"
"\n"
" [options]\n"
" Poco:shared=True\n"
" Poco:enable_apacheconnector=False\n"
" OpenSSL:shared=True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:96
msgid "Installation will be as easy as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../using_packages/using_profiles.rst:98
msgid "$ conan install . -pr=./poco_clang_3.5"
msgstr ""

